                     <interp inst="t17290709-63-person364" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
             had never seen him till Doyle brought her to Newgate with a Straw-Hat on; and objected against the Credit of 
               <persName id="t17290709-63-person365">
                  Arabella 
                  Manning 
               <interp inst="t17290709-63-person365" type="surname" value="Manning"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17290709-63-person365" type="given" value="Arabella"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17290709-63-person365" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , and call'd one 
               <persName id="t17290709-63-person366">
                  Ann 
                  Andrews 
               <interp inst="t17290709-63-person366" type="surname" value="Andrews"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17290709-63-person366" type="given" value="Ann"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17290709-63-person366" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , who depos'd, that she had heard Doyle say, he would be reveng'd on Wileman for threatening to take his Wife up for returning from Transportation: He also call'd some Evidence to his Reputation, who depos'd, that they knew him, and had never heard any Ill of him, and they took him to be an honest Man. But the Fact being prov'd to the Satisfaction of the Jury, they found him <rs id="t17290709-63-verdict326" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17290709-63-verdict326" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               guilty
            </rs> of this Indictment also.</p>
